Description: Ostracon, large section of the upper-body of a buff-coloured pottery wine-jar, the fabric contains many small white inclusions, the exterior is covered with a light-brown resinous deposit, now darkened in parts, and very faint traces of two lines of black-painted hieratic text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393628) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393628)
